snippet.title: Higher Higher - Traditional Outdoor Games Challenge For Kids - No 5 - Rain-shine
snippet.description:
Kids waterproofs from Rain-shine

http://www.rain-shine.co.uk

SIGN UP TO OUR ENEWSLETTER FOR YOUR FREE CHAPTER FROM OUR EBOOK ON MUDDY PLAY - VISIT WWW.RAIN-SHINE.CO.UK
Let your children have fun outside whatever the weather.  Rain-shine are the supplier of quality children's waterproof clothing throughout the UK.

We provide all in one waterproofs, all in one snowsuits, waterproof jackets, waterproof trousers and waterproof dungarees for children from age 9 months to 11 years. 

This summer our little Rain-shine team are trying out some traditional games.  Many of these simple games have been forgotten with time, and we want to see if kids can still have fun learning the games their parents and grandparents played.  

Skipping games have been around for hundreds of years.  It is thought that skipping was originally a boys game, being too strenuous for girls to play!  Higher-higher is not really skipping, but it does need a skipping rope and at least three people.  

Two people hold the rope stretched tightly.  The person in the middle has to jump the rope.  The rope becomes progressively higher with each jump until the player can no longer jump cleanly over the rope.  The person who can jump the highest wins.

Higher-higher can be enjoyed by children of any age, and can be as easy or as challenging as the players wish. This may have started out as a boys game, but our girls prove that they can jump higher too!  How high can you go?

For further information on our products just visit http://www.rain-shine.co.uk or email laura@rain-shine.co.uk

snippet.title: Kids using a parachute at an outdoor birthday party in Fairfield County | Athletic Parties
snippet.description:
Athletic Parties brings all of the fun and excitement of a P.E. class to your child's next birthday party. We believe in creating a positive and fun environment for kids to learn teamwork, cooperation, and motor movement. Our Kids Party Entertainment is offered in Westchester, Fairfield, and Rockland Counties.

Our Westchester Kid's Party Packages bring the fun and excitement of a Phys. Ed. Class to your next party or event. Our focus is on character building, with a "No Bullying Allowed" policy. The themes of our kid's fitness parties emphasize team work, sportsmanship, and positive reinforcement. We also address the importance of exercise, stretching, and healthy eating.

To learn more about how Athletic Parties brings the fun and excitement to your child's next party or event, visit www.athleticparties.com or call 914-318-0614.

snippet.description:

snippet.title: Horse Power For Kids | Outdoor Parks in Tampa
snippet.description: At Horse Power For Kids, Inc., we believe that "The outside of the horse is good for the inside of the man.". HorsePower for Kids Farm provides a means and the opportunity for People of all ages to interact with Horses, Ponies, and small Animals. We provide an equestrian based interaction, safety instruction and expectation understanding before riding begins. Equally important is the introduction to farm living and responsibilities through the petting, caring and feeding of the variety of animals at the farm. These lessons encourage self pride of accomplishment and goal setting through hands on learning and crafts. Located in Tampa, come by Horse Power For Kids today! For more information visit us online at www dot horse power for kids dot com. Visit LocalSaver.com to learn more!  http://www.localsaver.com/FL/Tampa/Horse_Power_For_Kids/BDSP-12604614.html

With ABC tag the players can call out a word starting with the first letter of the alphabet and continuing on to the next letter of the alphabet to avoid being tagged by the person who is it.
